Step 01
Discovery
We analyze and understand the client’s needs, the scope of the project, and the project’s objectives to ensure a successful no-code development journey.
Step 02
Project Planning​
Our team decides a timeframe, required resources, and milestones for a structured approach to efficiently accomplish project goals.
Step 03
Architecture & Design​
A proper design system is followed; wireframe is the first step, then we craft high fidelity mock-ups and, lastly, prototyping for the actual functioning of your project.
Step 04
MVP Launch
We perform back-end development based on database modeling and front-end development based on mock-ups and prototypes to deliver a functional, no-code solution.
Step 05
Development & Testing
Following development, our team will perform testing on various devices to ensure the efficiency of your project.
Step 06
Deployment & Setup
After thorough testing and completing the product, we deploy the generated solution effectively, and thus your final application is launched.
Step 07
After-Release Maintenance
After launching the application, we are available for post-launch maintenance, such as any technical support and plugin updates to enhance our user satisfaction.
Step 08
Continuous Support
Once the project is completed and delivered successfully, our no code development team is still up to provide on-going support afterwards.

FAQs

frequently asked questions

Can I convert my existing platform to low code/no code?
Yes, we will help you convert your existing platform to a low code/no code solution, depending on its complexity and suitability for migration. However, exact feature equality may not always be necessary for successful migration.
How long does it take to build a Low-code website?

Building a low-code website typically takes:

  • 4 weeks for a simple prototype
  • 10 weeks for a mid-level website
  • 12+ weeks for a complex website, 3 times faster than traditional coding.
Can my no code or low code solution ensure scalability and security?
Yes, your no code or low code solution can be scalable and secure with proper implementation, ensuring it meets your business’s evolving needs and data protection requirements.
How to choose the right no-code development platform?

Factors to Consider When Choosing the Right Low-Code Development Platform

  1. Identify use cases.
  2. Decide who will design the apps.
  3. Evaluate integration needs.
  4. Review DevOps, hosting, and governance.
  5. Consider pricing options.
How much does low-code development cost?
The expense usually starts from $3k-5k. This cost could become substantial when employing multiple tools, which might pose a significant financial commitment for individuals or smaller enterprises.
What Are The Benefits Of Using A No-Code Development Platform?
Businesses adopting no-code development platforms often experience enhanced internal productivity and time efficiency. Additionally, when introducing applications to users, these platforms can significantly reduce time-to-market.
